ComplexType.name: BasicIntervalSchedule
ComplexType.Comment: Schedule of values at points in time.

Simple.name: startTime
Simple.Comment: The time for the first time point.

ComplexType.name: ConductingEquipment
ComplexType.Comment: The parts of the power system that are designed to carry current or that are conductively connected through terminals.

ComplexType.name: CurrentFlow
ComplexType.Comment: Electrical current with sign convention: positive flow is out of the conducting equipment into the connectivity node.

Root.name: Curve
Root.Comment: A multi-purpose curve or functional relationship between an independent variable (X-axis) and dependent (Y-axis) variables.

Reference.name: curveStyle
Reference.Comment: The style or shape of the curve.

Root.name: CurveData
Root.Comment: Multi-purpose data points for defining a curve. The use of this generic class is discouraged if a more specific class can be used to specify the x and y axis values along with their specific data types.

Simple.name: xvalue
Simple.Comment: The data value of the X-axis variable, depending on the X-axis units.

Simple.name: y1value
Simple.Comment: The data value of the first Y-axis variable, depending on the Y-axis units.

Simple.name: y2value
Simple.Comment: The data value of the second Y-axis variable (if present), depending on the Y-axis units.

Simple.name: y3value
Simple.Comment: The data value of the third Y-axis variable (if present), depending on the Y-axis units.

Reference.name: Curve
Reference.Comment: The curve of this curve data point.

EnumeratedValue.name: constantYValue
EnumeratedValue.Comment: The Y-axis values are assumed constant until the next curve point and prior to the first curve point.

EnumeratedValue.name: formula
EnumeratedValue.Comment: An unspecified formula is assumed to compute the Y-axis value between points.

EnumeratedValue.name: rampYValue
EnumeratedValue.Comment: The Y-axis values are assumed to ramp between points.

EnumeratedValue.name: straightLineYValues
EnumeratedValue.Comment: The Y-axis values are assumed to be a straight line between values. Also known as linear interpolation.

ComplexType.name: Equipment
ComplexType.Comment: The parts of a power system that are physical devices, electronic or mechanical.

Simple.name: aggregate
Simple.Comment: The single instance of equipment represents multiple pieces of equipment that have been modeled together as an aggregate. Examples would be power transformers or sychronous machines operating in parallel modeled as a single aggregate power transformer or aggregate synchronous machine. This is not to be used to indicate equipment that is part of a group of interdependent equipment produced by a network production program.

Simple.name: normallyInService
Simple.Comment: If true, the equipment is normally in service.

Root.name: GroundDisconnector
Root.Comment: A manually operated or motor operated mechanical switching device used for isolating a circuit or equipment from Ground.

ComplexType.name: IdentifiedObject
ComplexType.Comment: This is a root class to provide common identification for all classes needing identification and naming attributes.

Simple.name: mRID
Simple.Comment: Master resource identifier issued by a model authority. The mRID is globally unique within an exchange context.
Global uniqeness is easily achived by using a UUID for the mRID. It is strongly recommended to do this.
For CIMXML data files in RDF syntax, the mRID is mapped to rdf:ID or rdf:about attributes that identify CIM object elements.

Simple.name: aliasName
Simple.Comment: The aliasName is free text human readable name of the object alternative to IdentifiedObject.name. It may be non unique and may not correlate to a naming hierarchy.

The attribute aliasName is retained because of backwards compatibility between CIM relases. It is however recommended to replace aliasName with the Name class as aliasName is planned for retirement at a future time.

Simple.name: name
Simple.Comment: The name is any free human readable and possibly non unique text naming the object.

ComplexType.name: IrregularIntervalSchedule
ComplexType.Comment: The schedule has time points where the time between them varies.

Root.name: IrregularTimePoint
Root.Comment: TimePoints for a schedule where the time between the points varies.

Simple.name: value1
Simple.Comment: The first value at the time. The meaning of the value is defined by the derived type of the associated schedule.

Simple.name: value2
Simple.Comment: The second value at the time. The meaning of the value is defined by the derived type of the associated schedule.

Reference.name: IntervalSchedule
Reference.Comment: An IrregularTimePoint belongs to an IrregularIntervalSchedule.

Reference.name: time
Reference.Comment: The time is relative to the schedule starting time.

Root.name: OutageSchedule
Root.Comment: The period of time that a piece of equipment is out of service, for example, for maintenance or testing; including the equipment's active power rating while under maintenance. The X-axis represents absolute time and the Y-axis represents the equipment's available rating while out of service.

ComplexType.name: PowerSystemResource
ComplexType.Comment: A power system resource can be an item of equipment such as a switch, an equipment container containing many individual items of equipment such as a substation, or an organisational entity such as sub-control area. Power system resources can have measurements associated.

Simple.name: value
Simple.Comment: Time, in seconds

ComplexType.name: Switch
ComplexType.Comment: A generic device designed to close, or open, or both, one or more electric circuits.

Simple.name: normalOpen
Simple.Comment: The attribute is used in cases when no Measurement for the status value is present. If the Switch has a status measurment the Discrete.normalValue is expected to match with the Switch.normalOpen.

Simple.name: retained
Simple.Comment: Branch is retained in a bus branch model.

Simple.name: switchOnCount
Simple.Comment: The switch on count since the switch was last reset or initialized.

Simple.name: switchOnDate
Simple.Comment: The date and time when the switch was last switched on.

Reference.name: ratedCurrent
Reference.Comment: The maximum continuous current carrying capacity in amps governed by the device material and construction.

Root.name: SwitchingOperation
Root.Comment: A SwitchingOperation is used to define individual switch operations for an OutageSchedule. This OutageSchedule may be associated with another item of Substation such as a Transformer, Line, or Generator; or with the Switch itself as a PowerSystemResource. A Switch may be referenced by many OutageSchedules.

Reference.name: newState
Reference.Comment: The switch position that shall result from this SwitchingOperation.

Simple.name: operationTime
Simple.Comment: Time of operation in same units as OutageSchedule.xAxixUnits.

Reference.name: OutageSchedule
Reference.Comment: An OutageSchedule may operate many switches.

EnumeratedType.name: UnitMultiplier
EnumeratedType.Comment: The unit multipliers defined for the CIM.

EnumeratedValue.name: none
EnumeratedValue.Comment: No multiplier or equivalently multiply by 1.

EnumeratedType.name: UnitSymbol
EnumeratedType.Comment: The units defiend for usage in the CIM.

EnumeratedValue.name: VAh
EnumeratedValue.Comment: Apparent energy in volt ampere hours.

EnumeratedValue.name: VAr
EnumeratedValue.Comment: Reactive power in volt ampere reactive.

EnumeratedValue.name: VArh
EnumeratedValue.Comment: Reactive energy in volt ampere reactive hours.

EnumeratedValue.name: degC
EnumeratedValue.Comment: Relative temperature in degrees Celsius. In the SI unit system the symbol is ºC. Electric charge is measured in coulomb that has the unit symbol C. To destinguish degree Celsius form coulomb the symbol used in the UML is degC. Reason for not using ºC is the special character º is difficult to manage in software.

EnumeratedValue.name: none
EnumeratedValue.Comment: Dimension less quantity, e.g. count, per unit, etc.
